article.headline: Maine 74, Stony Brook 66
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Kevin Reed scored 21 points to lead Maine to a 74-66 victory over Stony Brook on Thursday night. Junior Bernal added 19 points for the Black Bears (9-11, 4-4 America East), who held a 27-25 lead at halftime. Ricky Luca had a game-high 22 points for the Seawolves (7-13, 2-6). Emanuel Neto added 13 points and 16 rebounds for Stony Brook. The Seawolves jumped out to a 22-8 at 10:03 as Lucas connected on a pair of 3-pointers. Reed hit two 3 pointers as the Black Bears responded with a 17-5 run the remainder of the half. Bernal closed it out with a jumper with 14 seconds left. Maine opened the second half on 15-4 run to take command, 42-29 at 16:29.
